{
  "texts": [
    "Responsibility judgmentsAnother moral judgment that can be affected by anthropomorphism concerns attributions of moral responsibility.",
    "If AIs are attributed certain human capacities, then their possession could qualify them as morally responsible agents.",
    "For example, if AI is perceived as having a mind of its own, then this means that it can be viewed as capable of intentional action, and therefore, held responsible for its actions [36].",
    "For an entity to be morally responsible for its actions, it has to be a moral agent.",
    "At this point, it is important to note that having moral status, which was the judgment considered before, and being a moral agent are distinct."
  ]
}